title: Ole Miss kicks off against Auburn at 11 a.m. on Oct. 31
text:
Ole Miss kicks off against Auburn at 11 a.m. on Oct. 31 Daniel Paulling, The Clarion-Ledger 2:22 p.m. CDT October 19, 2015 Ole Miss kicks off Oct. 31 against Auburn at 11 a.m. (Photo: Spruce Derden, Spruce Derden-USA TODAY Sports) 1 CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
OXFORD — Ole Miss will kick off its Oct. 31 road game against Auburn at 11 a.m. 
It will be the Rebels’ fourth 11 a.m. kick this season, joining games against Memphis, New Mexico State and Tennessee-Martin. The game will be on either ESPN or SEC Network. 
Auburn (4-2, 1-2 SEC) leads the series 29-10 and is 14-2 against the Rebels at home. The Rebels haven’t won in Auburn since 2003 and have lost five of the last six in the series. 
The Rebels host Texas A&M on Saturday at 6 p.m., a game that will be broadcast on ESPN.
